goals.1: Identify the BGP to retrieve states that were monarchies and have been replaced by some other state
goals.2: Identify the BGP for obtaining statistical information of monarchies, e.g., poluation or inception date
goals.3: Which is or was  the country with the highest population?
goals.4: How many countries are or have been monarchies across continents?
goals.5: Analyze the number of countries that were monarchies
goals.5.1: How many sub-types of monarchy exist?  How many instances of exist of each one?
goals.5.2: Are there cities that have been capital of multiple kingdoms?
goals.5.3: Which are the top-3 monarchies with the earliest inception and still existing?

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname (COUNT(?p) AS ?number) WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; ?p ?obj. ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname. } GROUP BY ?p ?pname ORDER BY DESC (?number) LIMIT 100
output: located in the administrative territorial entity
office held by head of state
located in or next to body of water
Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names ID
category for people who died here
office held by head of government
located in present-day administrative territorial entity

2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?name ?inc ?curname (MAX(?pop) AS ?latest_pop) ?area WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269. OPTIONAL{?mon wdt:P571 ?inc.} OPTIONAL{?mon wdt:P38 ?cur.} OPTIONAL{?mon wdt:P1082 ?pop.} OPTIONAL{?mon wdt:P2046 ?area.} ?mon <http://schema.org/name> ?name. ?cur <http://schema.org/name> ?curname. } GROUP BY ?name ?inc ?curname ?area
output: Coins and postage stamps of Sealand
Kingdom of Spain under Joseph Bonaparte
Croatia in personal union with Hungary
Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant
Austro-Hungarian rule in Bosnia and Herzegovina
United Kingdom of Portugal, Brazil and the Algarves
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland
Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant
Gay and Lesbian Kingdom of the Coral Sea Islands
Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes

2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?name ?date ?latest_pop (GROUP_CONCAT(?curname;separator=",") as ?currencies) WHERE { ?mon wdt:P38 ?cur. {SELECT ?mon (MIN(?inc) AS ?date) WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P571 ?inc. }GROUP BY ?mon } {SELECT ?mon2 (MAX(?pop) AS ?latest_pop) WHERE { ?mon2 (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P1082 ?pop. }GROUP BY ?mon2 } ?mon <http://schema.org/name> ?name. ?cur <http://schema.org/name> ?curname. FILTER(?mon=?mon2) }
output: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland
Austro-Hungarian rule in Bosnia and Herzegovina
Umayyad fals (currency unit),Umayyad dinar (currency unit),Umayyad dirham (currency unit)
Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes
Coins and postage stamps of Sealand
Australian pound,Australian dollar,Solomon Islands dollar,pound sterling,Solomon Islands pound

2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?name ?inception ?latest_pop ?area WHERE { {SELECT ?mon (MIN(?inc) AS ?inception) WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P571 ?inc. }GROUP BY ?mon } {SELECT ?mon2 (MAX(?pop) AS ?latest_pop) WHERE { ?mon2 (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P1082 ?pop. }GROUP BY ?mon2 } {SELECT ?mon3 (MAX(?a) AS ?area) WHERE { ?mon3 (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P2046 ?a. }GROUP BY ?mon3 } ?mon <http://schema.org/name> ?name. FILTER(?mon=?mon2 && ?mon2=?mon3) }
output: Austro-Hungarian rule in Bosnia and Herzegovina
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland
Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes

3.query: SELECT ?country ?pop WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P1082 ?pop. ?mon <http://schema.org/name> ?country. } ORDER BY DESC (?pop) LIMIT 1

4.query: SELECT ?continent (COUNT(DISTINCT ?mon) AS ?number) WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P30 ?con. ?mon <http://schema.org/name> ?country. ?con <http://schema.org/name> ?continent. } GROUP BY ?continent ORDER BY DESC (?number)

4.narrative: WRONG QUERY, COUNTRY IS A PREDICATE NOT AN ENTITY

4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?pname (COUNT(?p) AS ?number) WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; ?p ?obj. ?p <http://schema.org/name> ?pname. } GROUP BY ?p ?pname ORDER BY DESC(?number)
SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} }
SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} }

SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname WHERE { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P1366+ ?country. ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} }

SELECT DISTINCT ?continent (COUNT(?country) AS ?number) WHERE { ?country wdt:P30 ?con. { SELECT DISTINCT ?country WHERE { { ?mon (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P1366+ ?country. ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} } UNION { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} } } } ?con <http://schema.org/name> ?continent. } GROUP BY ?continent ORDER BY DESC (?number)

output: crown land of the Austrian Empire
emirate of the United Arab Emirates

5.1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?type (COUNT(?country) AS ?number) WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* ?o. ?o wdt:P279 wd:Q7269. ?o <http://schema.org/name> ?type. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} } GROUP BY(?type) ORDER BY DESC (?number)

SELECT DISTINCT ?capitalname (COUNT (DISTINCT ?p) AS ?kingdoms) WHERE{ ?p (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P36 ?capital. ?capital <http://schema.org/name> ?capitalname. }GROUP BY (?capitalname) HAVING ((COUNT (DISTINCT ?p)) > 1) ORDER BY DESC (?kingdoms)

SELECT DISTINCT ?countryname ?inception WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P571 ?inception. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} }

SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryname WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P571 ?inception. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} } ORDER BY ASC (?inception) LIMIT 3

SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryname WHERE { ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256; (wdt:P31|wdt:P122)/wdt:P279* wd:Q7269; wdt:P571 ?inception. ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryname. FILTER (NOT EXISTS{?country wdt:P576 ?obj.} && ?country!=wd:Q756617) } ORDER BY ASC (?inception) LIMIT 3
